// LPF (low-pass filter) test
// Hear the filter: bright saw without LPF vs. same with LPF cutting highs.
//
// Where LPF comes from:
// - Pattern API: @strudel/core (controls: .lpf(freq), .lpq(resonance), .ftype('ladder'|'12db'|'24db'))
// - Audio: superdough (cutoff → lpf node frequency; createFilter → BiquadFilter or ladder-processor)
// - DSP: superdough/worklets.mjs → LadderProcessor (AudioWorklet) when .ftype('ladder')
//
setcps(0.5)

// Test 1: Saw with fixed LPF — should sound duller (highs cut at 800 Hz)
s("saw").note("c2").lpf(800).lpq(2)

// Test 2: Uncomment to compare — no LPF (full brightness)
// s("saw").note("c2")

// Test 3: LPF sweep (cutoff moves 400 → 2000 over 8 cycles) — hear filter open/close
// s("saw").note("c2").lpf(sine.range(400,2000).slow(8)).lpq(3)

